and make community connections.\u00a0 \u00a0<\/p>\n<p>[\/et_pb_text][et_pb_text module_class=&#8221;tick-list-green&#8221; _builder_version=&#8221;4.16&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; link_font=&#8221;||||on||||&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p>The primary aim of our Community Chest is to fund projects that reduce social isolation, support people\u2019s physical and mental wellbeing, and help people feel more connected to the area they live. We accept a wide range of project ideas that help do this and have funded art sessions, community walks, dance, music, youth clubs, lunch clubs, community keep fit and even circus skills for kids.<\/p>\n<p>[\/et_pb_text][\/et_pb_column][\/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version=&#8221;4.16&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; max_width=&#8221;720px&#8221; custom_margin=&#8221;|auto|30px|auto|false|false&#8221; locked=&#8221;off&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][et_pb_column type=&#8221;4_4&#8243; _builder_version=&#8221;4.16&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][et_pb_image src=&#8221;https:\/\/wmbiglocal.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/Russell-Rd-Queens-Jubilee-party-Photo-Credit-to-Matt-Reynolds.jpg&#8221; alt=&#8221;Russell Rd Queen&#8217;s Jubilee party, people playing Tug of War &#8221; title_text=&#8221;Russell Rd Queen&#8217;s Jubilee party -Photo Credit to Matt Reynolds&#8221; _builder_version=&#8221;4.16&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][\/et_pb_image][\/et_pb_column][\/et_pb_row][et_pb_row column_structure=&#8221;2_5,3_5&#8243; make_equal=&#8221;on&#8221; _builder_version=&#8221;4.16&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#FFFFFF&#8221; max_width=&#8221;720px&#8221; custom_margin=&#8221;||||false|false&#8221; custom_padding=&#8221;18px|12px|18px|12px|true|true&#8221; border_width_bottom=&#8221;1px&#8221; border_color_bottom=&#8221;#E0E0E0&#8243; locked